{"cursor":"3792","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Analog device' is usually a combination of both analog machine and analog media\nthat can together measure, record, or reproduce (emit) continuous information,\nfor example, the almost infinite number of grades of transparency, voltage,\nresistance, rotation, or pressure. In theory, the continuous information (also\nanalog signal) has an infinite number of possible values with the only\nlimitation on resolution being the accuracy of the analog device.\n","linknr":126,"url":"Analog_device","recorded":1362669395,"links":14,"instances":["optics","measurement","mathematics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Analog circuits","Electronic circuits","Electronic engineering"],"headings":["Examples","Interfacing the digital and analog worlds","Controversy over Photographic Film","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["continuum","measurement"],["transparency","optics"],["value","mathematics"]],"members":["transparency","continuum","value"],"related":["Machine","Recording_media","Measurement","Recording","Emit","Continuum_(measurement)","Information","Transparency_(optics)","Voltage","Electrical_resistance","Rotation","Pressure","Analog_signal","Value_(mathematics)","Angular_resolution","Accuracy","Clock","Telautograph","Analog_synthesizer","Analog_computer","Analog_television","Analog_computer","Digital-to-analog_converter","Digital_signal","Analog-to-digital_converter","Digital-to-analog_converter"]}